headlines.description: Theo Pinson scored 14 of his 16 points after halftime to go with 10 rebounds, helping No. 14 North Carolina pull away late to beat Notre Dame 83-66 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 14 North Carolina pulls away late, tops Notre Dame 83-66

video.headline: UNC comes away with home victory

headlines.description: Teddy Allen scored 16 points, giving No. 20 West Virginia a needed spark off the bench in an 82-66 victory over TCU on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Strong bench scoring helps No. 20 WVU beat TCU 82-66

headlines.description: Jared Sam scored 18 points and grabbed 15 rebounds to help Southern beat Mississippi Valley State 55-51 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sam's double-double leads Southern past MVSU 55-51

headlines.description: Francis Alonso had 20 points and Demetrius Troy scored 17 to help UNC Greensboro beat East Tennessee State 74-56 on Monday night to pull within one game of the Buccaneers in the Southern Conference standings.
headlines.shortLinkText: UNCG beats ETSU 74-56, snaps nation's longest win streak

headlines.description: Jermaine Crumpton had 21 points and 10 rebounds on Monday night and Canisius pulled away early in the second half for an 81-63 win over Fairfield.
headlines.shortLinkText: Canisius ties for 1st in MAAC with 81-63 win over Fairfield

headlines.description: Evan Fisher had 10 of his 21 points in overtime, including two free throws with 12.4 seconds left, to help Siena beat Iona 82-78 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fisher's 10 points in OT help Siena get past Iona 82-78

headlines.description: Kimbal Mackenzie scored six of his 11 points in the final 21 seconds, including the winning 3-pointer as time expired, to help Bucknell rally for a 65-64 win over Colgate on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mackenzie 3s caps late spurt, lifts Bucknell over Colgate

video.headline: Bucknell uses incredible comeback, buzzer-beater to top Colgate

headlines.description: Kyle Williams scored 20 points, Derrik Jamerson Jr. added 19 and each made five 3-pointers in Norfolk State's 93-58 victory over Delaware State on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Norfolk State hits 14 3-pointers, beats Delaware State 93-58

headlines.description: Brandon Tabb scored 25 points with four steals, Isaiah Bailey added 22 points and eight assists and Bethune-Cookman beat North Carolina Central 99-81 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bethune-Cookman coasts to 99-81 win over NC Central

headlines.description: Jermaine Marrow scored 23 points, Malique Trent-Street added 20 with four 3-pointers in the second half and Hampton beat Coppin State 82-79 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hampton grinds out 82-79 win over Coppin State

headlines.description: Charles Williams scored 28 points on Monday night, RJ Cole had 18 points, nine rebounds, six assists and two steals and Howard used three big first-half runs to pull away for an 84-56 win over Maryland-Eastern Shore.
headlines.shortLinkText: Howard cruises to 84-56 win over Maryland-Eastern Shore

headlines.description: Ross Cummings hit four 3-pointers and finished with 21 points and Jordan Strawberry had 18 points, six rebounds, seven assists and two steals to help Mercer beat Samford 74-69 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cummings hits 4 3s, scores 21; Mercer beats Samford 74-69

headlines.description: Tiwian Kendley scored 24 points and Morgan State held Florida A&M to 18 first-half points on its way to a 74-48 win on Monday night.
Javaris Jenkins scored 21 points, made 4 of 6 from 3-point range and blocked three shots Monday night to help Savannah State beat North Carolina A&T 108-106.
headlines.shortLinkText: Savannah State beats NC A&T in MEAC showdown

headlines.description: A.J. Mosby had 22 points on 9-of-11 shooting, including 4 of 5 from 3-point range, and Dante Sterling scored 15 points to help Alcorn State beat Arkansas-Pine Bluff 84-52 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mosby scores 22, Alcorn State hits 12 3s in win over UAPB

headlines.description: Jo Lual-Acuil Jr.'s follow-up dunk with 8 seconds left in double overtime sent Baylor to a 74-73 win over Texas on Monday night, the fourth straight victory for the resurgent Bears after a miserable start to the Big 12 season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor tops Texas 74-73 in double OT

headlines.description: Ivy Smith Jr. had 22 points and seven rebounds on Monday night to help Grambling beat Texas Southern 78-55 for its 10th straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grambling wins 10th straight, beats Texas Southern 78-55

headlines.description: Dennis Jones had 22 points and Zachary Hamilton scored five of his 11 points in overtime to help Prairie View A&M beat Jackson State 63-58 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones, Hamilton help PVAMU beat Jackson St. 63-58 in OT

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "I’m getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. It’s a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how I’m going to dictate how my team wins. … It’s a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... It’s a process. Right now, it’s tough."
